@HostAddress = https://localhost:8443
@Token = {{$processEnv JWT_DEV_TOKEN}}

### Anonymous liveness probe.
GET {{HostAddress}}/healthz

### Aspire-only health rollup (Development environment only, see MapDefaultEndpoints).
GET {{HostAddress}}/health

### Get the latest cached Bitcoin prices.
# The background service (BitCoinApiService) polls CoinGecko on ExternalAPISettings:Interval
# and caches the result; this just reads the cache via BitcoinPriceQueryService.
#
# Requires a bearer token because BaseController is [Authorize]. Generate one with:
#   export JWT_DEV_TOKEN=$(./scripts/generate-dev-jwt.sh)
# then re-open/re-run this request so the REST Client extension picks up the env var.
# (VS Code: humao.rest-client. Visual Studio 2022 17.11+ has native .http support too,
# but reads variables from http-client.env.json instead of $processEnv — see README below.)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/bitcoin/latest
Authorization: Bearer {{Token}}

### Same request, explicit alternate route.
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/bitcoin
Authorization: Bearer {{Token}}

# ---
# Run the whole stack through Aspire (recommended, gives you traces/metrics/logs), requires Docker
# since the AppHost provisions the "cache" Redis container:
#   dotnet run --project src/BitCoin.AppHost
# Open the Aspire dashboard link printed in the console. Two resources will be running:
#   - "cache"       the Redis container backing IDistributedCache.
#   - "bitcoin-api" this API.
# Fire these requests and watch:
#   - Traces: BitcoinPriceIndex.Fetch span (custom) with a nested HTTP GET span to
#     api.coingecko.com, plus the inbound ASP.NET Core request span for /api/v1/bitcoin/latest,
#     which itself nests a Redis GET span (from Aspire.StackExchange.Redis.DistributedCaching).
#   - Metrics: bitcoin.price_fetch.success/failure, bitcoin.price_fetch.duration,
#     bitcoin.price.latest (gauge), plus the built-in ASP.NET Core/HttpClient/runtime metrics.
#   - Logs: cache set/hit/miss entries (BitCoin.API.Services.RedisCacheProvider) and the
#     historical-fetch request/response entries (BitCoin.API.Services.BitcoinPriceIndexClient),
#     all correlated to the same trace ID (Debug level, already enabled for BitCoin.API.* in
#     appsettings.Development.json).
#   - Health: /health now also reports Redis reachability (AspNetCore.HealthChecks.Redis),
#     wired up automatically by the Aspire Redis client integration.
